{"lemma":"عُرْفُ","slug":"عُرْفُ","root":"ع.ر.ف","root_slug":"ع-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عُرْف","root":"عرف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28733","n28734","n28735","n28736"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be familiar with (a person, a place, a piece of news or information, and so on); to know","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"هَلْ تَعْرِفُهَا؟","english":"Do you know her?"},{"text":"أَعْرِفُ أَنَّهَا دَرَسَتِ الْحُقُوقَ.","english":"I know that she studied law."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be familiar with (a skill or profession); to be experienced in; to be proficient at or in; can","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"هُوَ عَارِفٌ بِالْيَابَانِيَّةِ","english":"He is proficient in Japanese."},{"text":"أَعْرِفُ الْعَزْفَ وَالْغِنَاءَ.","english":"I know how to sing and play music."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to recognise (a person, a place, and so on); to identify; to recall","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":".أَرَيْتُهَا صُورَتَهُ فَلَمْ تَعْرِفْهُ","english":"I showed her his picture, but she could not recognize him."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become aware of; to find out","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"فَعَرَفْتُ أَنَّهُ كاذِبٌ.","english":"That is when I knew he was lying."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to define","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tell about, to inform of, to make aware of; to acquaint with, to introduce to","tags":["ditransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a practice that is widely known somewhere or in some group; a convention; custom; a tradition","tags":["countable","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the crest or comb of a rooster, a cockscomb; any tuftlike protuberance; an outgrowth","tags":["countable","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the crest or comb of a rooster, a cockscomb; the forelock of a horse","tags":["countable","transitive","uncommon"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scent, aroma","tags":["countable","transitive"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.ra.fa/","/ʕar.ra.fa/","/ʕurf/","/ʕarf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28733","headword_ar":"عَرْفٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An odour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fragrant"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fetid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,) in most instances the former, (K, TA,) as when it is used in relation to Paradise: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarofapN","text_ar":"عَرْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [the same, i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TK) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iHapN","text_ar":"رَايِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TK.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA A^aToyaba","text_ar":"ما اَطْيَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earofahu","text_ar":"عَرْفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How fragrant is its odour!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaEojizu masoku Als~awo'i Eano Earofi Als~awo'i","text_ar":"لَا يَعْجِزُ مَسْكُ السَّوْءِ عَنْ عَرْفِ السَّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bad hide will not lack the fetid odour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, K;) a prov.; (S, O;) applied to the low, ignoble, mean, or sordid, who will not cease from his evil doing; he being likened to the hide that is not fit for being tanned; (O, K;) wherefore it is cast aside, and becomes fetid. (O.) And some read, in the Kur [lxxvii. 1],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lomurosalaAti EarofFA","text_ar":"وَا@لْمُرْسَلَاتِ عَرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By the winds that are sent forth with fragrance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofFA","text_ar":"عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumaAm","text_ar":"ثُمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panic grass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant, not of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ibn-'Abbád, O, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumaAm","text_ar":"ثُمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-'Abbád, O, L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n28734","headword_ar":"عُرْفٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Acknowledgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAiEotiraAfu","text_ar":"الاِعْتِرَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,) as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iqoraAru","text_ar":"الاـِقْرَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence, (S, O,) you say, (K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EalaY~a A^alofN","text_ar":"لَهُ عَلَىَّ اَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofFA","text_ar":"عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotiraAfFA","text_ar":"اِعْتِرَافًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thousand is due to him on my part by acknowlegment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confession"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, * K;) the last word being a corroborative. (S, O.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArifapN","text_ar":"عَارِفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaArifu","text_ar":"عَوَارِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukorN","text_ar":"نُكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"being contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munokarN","text_ar":"مُنْكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukorN","text_ar":"نُكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mgh, O, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a good quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lenity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favour, kindness, or bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a benefit, a benefaction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an act of beneficence"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kindness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also expl. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurufN","text_ar":"عُرُفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a dial. var. thereof: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing liberally,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freely, bestowed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"given:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"when it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with moderation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a right and just aim:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and sometimes it means simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moderation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest, advice"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counsel"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fellowship with one's family and with others of mankind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates: (TA:) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deed, of which the goodness is known by reason and by the law;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munokarN","text_ar":"مُنْكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the contr. thereof. (Er-Rághib, TA.) It is said in the Kur [vii. 198],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^omuro biA@loEurofi","text_ar":"وَاْمُرْ بِا@لْعُرْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And enjoin thou goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is deemed good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved, of actions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaAhu EurofFA","text_ar":"اَوْلَاهُ عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArifapF","text_ar":"عَارِفَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfFA","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conferred upon him, a benefit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, O, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walilomuTal~aqaAti","text_ar":"وَلِلْمُطَلَّقَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataAEN biA@lomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"مَتَاعٌ بِا@لْمَعْرُوفِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur ii. 242] means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And for the divorced women"},{"kind":"text","text":"there shall be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a provision of necessaries"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with moderation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right and just aim, and beneficence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawolN maEoruwfN","text_ar":"قَوْلٌ مَعْرُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamagofirapN xayorN mino SadaqapK yatobaEuhaA A^a*FY","text_ar":"وَمَغْفِرَةٌ خَيْرٌ مِنْ صَدَقَةٍ يَتْبَعُهَا اَذًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the same, ii. 265,] means Refusal with"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gracious"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expressed to the beggar, that God may sustain him,] (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and forgiveness"},{"kind":"text","text":"granted to the beggar for his importunity (Bd, Jel) or obtained by such refusal from God or from the beggar, (Bd,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are better than an alms which annoyance follows"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) by reproach for a benefit conferred and for begging. (Jel.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano kaAna faqiyrFA faloyaA^okulo","text_ar":"مَنْ كَانَ فَقِيرًا فَلْيَاْكُلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@lomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"بِا@لْمَعْرُوفِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the same, iv. 6,] means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And such as is poor, let him take for himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eat"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to what is approved by reason and by the law,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to his need"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the recompense of his labour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEurofu","text_ar":"العُرْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in lexicology, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The commonly-known, commonly-received,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common conventional, language; common parlance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common usage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"mostly meaning that of a whole people; in which case, the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAm~u","text_ar":"العَامُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes added: but often meaning that of a particular class; as, for instance, of the lawyers. Hence the terms"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaqiyqapN","text_ar":"حَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofFA","text_ar":"عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majaAzN EurofFA","text_ar":"مَجَازٌ عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hq","text_ar":"حق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jwz","text_ar":"جوز"},{"kind":"text","text":". See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaEaArafN","text_ar":"مُتَعَارَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eurof","text_ar":"عُرْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse; (S, O;) [i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mane;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2015},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that grows on the ridge"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the neck"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse (Mgh, Msb, K) or similar beast; (Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurufN","text_ar":"عُرُفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEorafapN","text_ar":"مَعْرَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part, of the neck, which is the place of growth of the hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see again"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEorafapN","text_ar":"مَعْرَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part, of the neck"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a bird],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the place of growth of the feathers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feathers"},{"kind":"text","text":"themselves"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the neck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense in the K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brl","text_ar":"برل"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is shown by the context therein:] and the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comb"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elongated piece of flesh on the upper part of the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a cock; to which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baZor","text_ar":"بَظْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a girl is likened: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAfN","text_ar":"اَعْرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly a pl. of pauc.] (O, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwfN","text_ar":"عُرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) As used it in relation to a man, explaining the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN muboravil~FA lil$~ar~i","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ مُبْرَثِلًّا لِلشَّرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAfi$FA Eurofahu","text_ar":"نَافِشًا عُرْفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruffling the feathers of his neck to do evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And [hence] it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA kaA^an~ahumo EurufN","text_ar":"جَاوُوا كَاَنَّهُمْ عُرُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came as though they were a mane"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"following one another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA=' Alqawomu EurofFA EurofFA","text_ar":"جَا=ء القَوْمُ عُرْفًا عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, came"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one after another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAra AlqaTaA EurofFA","text_ar":"طَارَ القَطَا عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sand-grouse flew"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one after another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lomurosalaAti EurofFA","text_ar":"وَا@لْمُرْسَلَاتِ عُرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) in the Kur [lxxvii. 1], a metaphorical phrase, from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eurof","text_ar":"عُرْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse, meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By the angels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the winds, that are sent forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consecutively, like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the several portions of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eurof","text_ar":"عُرْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mane"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the horse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sent forth"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@lomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"بِا@لْمَعْرُوفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with beneficence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [for further explanations, see the expositions of Z and Bd or others: and see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rsl","text_ar":"رسل"},{"kind":"text","text":":] some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarofFA","text_ar":"عَرْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in the next preceding paragraph]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence also,] (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waves of the sea."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Elevated sand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurufN","text_ar":"عُرُفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofapN","text_ar":"عُرْفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. (of the last, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurafN","text_ar":"عُرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (of the first, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAfN","text_ar":"اَعْرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) and all signify likewise (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and the first, (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overtopping, back"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a portion of sand, (K, TA,) and of a mountain, and of anything high: and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the earth or ground: and [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAfN","text_ar":"اَعْرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harov","text_ar":"حَرْث"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land ploughed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared, for sowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is upon the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"channels for irrigation that are called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulojaAn","text_ar":"فُلْجَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falajN","text_ar":"فَلَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawaAy^id","text_ar":"قَوَايِد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAy^idN","text_ar":"قَايِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [The pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEoraAfu","text_ar":"الاَعْرَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) mentioned in the Kur [vii. 44 and 46], (S, O,) is applied to (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wall between Paradise and Hell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) so it is said: (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the upper parts of the wall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlA^aEoraAfi","text_ar":"عَلَى الاَعْرَافِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be there meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY maEorifapi A^aholi Aljan~api waA^aholi Aln~aAri","text_ar":"عَلَى مَعْرِفَةِ اَهْلِ الجَنَّةِ وَاَهْلِ النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and possessing knowledge of the people of Paradise and of the people of Hell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it seems that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHotawuwna","text_ar":"مُحْتَوُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the like, is to be understood before"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY","text_ar":"على"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Zj, TA.) [And hence it is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Seventh Chapter of the Kur-án."},{"kind":"text","text":"] By"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbu AlA^aEoraAfi","text_ar":"اَصْحَابُ الاَعْرَافِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The occupants of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AErAf","text_ar":"اعراف"},{"kind":"text","text":"], there mentioned, are said to be meant persons whose good and evil works have been equal, so that they shall not have merited Paradise by the former nor Hell by the latter: or prophets: or angels. (Zj, TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofapN","text_ar":"عُرْفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-  [The pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAfN","text_ar":"اَعْرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"higher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foremost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) of winds; (K, TA;) and likewise of clouds, and of mists. (TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also, (As, O, K,) in the speech of the people of El-Bahreyn, (As, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"variety"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of palm-trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, O, K;) and so [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAfN","text_ar":"اَعْرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) is expl. by IDrd: (O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they first yield fruit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edible fruit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ripe fruit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they attain to doing so:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sort of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palmtree in El-Bahreyn, also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buro$uwm","text_ar":"بُرْشُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) but this is what is meant by As and IDrd. (TA.) ―         -b8-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^utoruj~","text_ar":"اُتْرُجّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"citrus medica,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"citron"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)       -A3-  Also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwfN","text_ar":"عَرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEorafu","text_ar":"اَعْرَفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarofaA='u","text_ar":"عَرْفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","Msb","Bd","Jel","Mgh","As"]},{"entry_id":"n28735","headword_ar":"عِرْفٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, is from the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Earafa","text_ar":"مَا عَرَفَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EirofiY A_il~aA biA^axarapK","text_ar":"عِرْفِى اـِلَّا بِاَخَرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did not know me save at the last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lastly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latterly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)       -A2-  And it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Patience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.) A poet says, (namely Aboo-Dahbal ElJumahee, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qulo liA@boni qayosK A^axiY Alr~uqay~aAti\n                      \n                     \n                        maA A^aHosana AlEirofa fiY AlmuSiybaAti"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Say thou to the son of Keys, the brother of Er-Rukeiyat, How good is patience in afflictions!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n28736","headword_ar":"عُرُفٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}